const publishDate = new Date("May 11 2026");
const author = "The Valley Clean Team";
const readTime = "5 min read";

const isPublished = new Date().getTime() >= publishDate.getTime();

---

<BaseLayout
  title="Bi-Weekly vs Monthly House Cleaning: Which?"
  description={isPublished ? "Full Article: Bi-Weekly vs. Monthly House Cleaning: Which is Right for You?" : "Coming Soon: Bi-Weekly vs. Monthly House Cleaning: Which is Right for You?"}
  noindex={!isPublished}
  ogImage="https://storage.googleapis.com/msgsndr/iKQIBhpKVL2XVPgU7HMd/media/6920802945dc047d65b4ec5d.png"
>
  <SchemaMarkup
    type="article"
    title="Bi-Weekly vs. Monthly House Cleaning: Which is Right for You?"
    description="Deciding between bi-weekly and monthly house cleaning? Learn which professional cleaning schedule best fits your lifestyle, budget, and household needs."
    publishDate="May 11 2026"
    author={author}
  />
  <!-- Hero Section -->
  <section class="pt-24 pb-16 bg-gradient-to-br from-gray-900 via-gray-800 to-gray-900">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="text-center">
        <span class="inline-block px-4 py-2 bg-[#FFA985]/20 text-[#FFA985] rounded-full text-sm font-medium mb-6">
          Pricing/Value
        </span>
        <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl lg:text-6xl font-bold text-white mb-6 leading-tight">
          Bi-Weekly vs. Monthly House Cleaning: Which is Right for You?
        </h1>
        <p class="text-xl text-gray-300 mb-8 max-w-2xl mx-auto">
          {isPublished ? "Expert Cleaning Guide" : "Coming May 11 2026."}
        </p>
        <div class="flex items-center justify-center space-x-4 text-gray-400 mb-8">
          <span>May 11 2026</span>
          <span>•</span>
          <span>{readTime}</span>
          <span>•</span>
          <span>By {author}</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Main Content Toggle based on Published Date -->
  {isPublished ? (
    <article class="py-16 bg-white">
      <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
        <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none">
          <!-- TODO: REPLACE THIS SECTION WITH YOUR ACTUAL BLOG CONTENT -->
          <h2>Bi-Weekly vs. Monthly House Cleaning: Which is Right for You?</h2>
<p><strong>Deciding between bi-weekly and monthly house cleaning services hinges on your lifestyle, budget, and specific cleaning needs. In The Shoals & Surrounding Areas, discerning residents often choose bi-weekly cleaning for consistent upkeep, while others opt for monthly services to fit a more relaxed schedule. The Valley Clean Team is here to help you find the perfect balance.</strong></p>
<p>Whether you’re a busy professional, a parent juggling multiple responsibilities, or someone who values a pristine home, understanding the differences and benefits of bi-weekly versus monthly cleaning is crucial. Let's dive into what each service entails and how it fits into your life in The Shoals & Surrounding Areas.</p>

<h3>Understanding Bi-Weekly Cleaning</h3>
<p>Bi-weekly cleaning means our trained cleaning specialists visit your home every other week. This schedule is perfect for those who:</p>
<ul>
  <li>Desire consistent cleanliness and tidiness</li>
  <li>Have pets or children that contribute to daily messes</li>
  <li>Prefer a more frequent, systematic cleaning approach</li>
</ul>
<p>With bi-weekly cleaning, you benefit from a home that always feels fresh and inviting. Our specialists follow precise checklists, ensuring nothing is overlooked. The investment in bi-weekly services often results in less time spent on daily maintenance, freeing you to enjoy your weekends.</p>

<h3>The Case for Monthly Cleaning</h3>
<p>Monthly cleaning is a viable option for those who maintain a tidy home but need occasional help to tackle deeper cleaning tasks. Consider monthly services if you:</p>
<ul>
  <li>Have a smaller household with minimal mess</li>
  <li>Prefer to handle regular cleaning yourself but need a hand with more intensive tasks</li>
  <li>Are budget-conscious but still value professional care</li>
</ul>
<p>Monthly cleaning offers thorough, professional attention to detail. It's ideal for those who want to complement their personal cleaning efforts with professional-grade results, ensuring the home remains well-maintained over time.</p>

<h3>Pricing and Value: What to Expect</h3>
<p>The Valley Clean Team provides transparent pricing tailored to your needs. In The Shoals & Surrounding Areas, our bi-weekly services start at a competitive rate, reflecting the value of consistent, high-standard cleaning. Monthly services are priced to offer maximum impact with less frequency but no compromise on quality.</p>
<p>Both options are investments in your home’s upkeep and your peace of mind. Our guaranteed services mean you can trust that every visit will meet our high standards, ensuring your satisfaction every step of the way.</p>

<h3>Choosing the Right Frequency for Your Home</h3>
<p>To decide between bi-weekly and monthly cleaning, consider the following:</p>
<ul>
  <li>**Lifestyle:** How much time do you spend at home, and how often do guests visit?</li>
  <li>**Budget:** What is your monthly budget for cleaning services?</li>
  <li>**Personal Preference:** Do you prefer consistent upkeep or are you comfortable with occasional deep cleans?</li>
</ul>
<p>Remember, there's no one-size-fits-all solution. It's about what works best for you and your family. The Valley Clean Team is committed to helping you make the choice that aligns with your lifestyle and expectations.</p>

<h3>Reclaim Your Time with The Valley Clean Team</h3>
<p>Your home deserves nothing less than the best. Whether you choose bi-weekly or monthly cleaning, The Valley Clean Team delivers precision and accountability. Stop worrying about house cleaning and reclaim your time. <strong>Book your guaranteed service with us today and experience the difference our veteran-owned team brings to The Shoals & Surrounding Areas.</strong></p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </article>
  ) : (
    <article class="py-16 bg-white border-t border-gray-100 shadow-inner">
      <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-12 bg-gray-50 rounded-2xl">
        <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none text-center">
          <Icon name="clock" class="w-16 h-16 text-[#FFA985] mx-auto mb-6" />
          <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-800 mb-4 mt-0">Article Coming Soon!</h2>
          <p class="text-gray-600 m-0">This article is locked and scheduled to automatically publish on <br/><strong class="text-gray-800 text-xl">May 11 2026</strong>.<br/>Check back then!</p>
          <div class="mt-12">
            <a href="/blog" class="inline-flex items-center justify-center px-6 py-3 text-lg font-semibold text-white bg-[#FFA985] rounded-full hover:bg-[#ff9a70] transition shadow-md no-underline">
              Back to Blog
            </a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </article>
  )}
